Best place for wings hands down. People who wait for delivery expect hot & ready food to the front door and it doesn't work that way. Hot & ready..lol...even Lil Caesar's hot & ready is only hot when eaten at the restaurant. We've ordered from WING WAGON for years albeit before wings become popular except for Chinese wings.  We usually order 40 or 50 without sauce in bottom of pan (that's the trick) to feed our family and/or guests.  Make sides at home and BOOM that's dinner! Stop crying cry babies. You don't wanna wait on delivery-pick it up yourselves.  These are Brooklyn's finest small business wings. Family owned business. Roots in the community.  We call in our order then pick up-eat some on trip home. That's how you do it.
